Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_voltus_insight_mode(25.10)                  set_voltus_insight_mode(25.10)

Name
       set_voltus_insight_mode

Syntax
       set_voltus_insight_mode

       [-help]

       -config <filename>

       [-db_mapping <filename>]

       -domain  <name>

       [-hier_block_instance  <names>]

       [-hierarchical {true | false}]

       [-import_analysis_data {true | false}]

       [-ir_effort {high||medium||low}]

       [-nParallel <value> ]

       [-scenario_default <list>]

       [-skip]

       [-timing_effort {high||medium||low}]

       [-watch_box  ]

       [-watch_inst ]

       Specifies  the  user-defined  settings  related to the Voltus InsightAI
       flow. The command allows you to configure flows for various  scenarios,
       such as differing EIV method, EIV evaluation window, and thresholds for
       each  instance type. Using this command, you can tailor your configura-
       tions precisely, ensuring optimal performance for every scenario.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each set_voltus_insight_mode parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command man set_voltus_insight_mode.

       -config <filename>
              (Mandatory)  Specifies  the  name of the configuration file that
              includes details about the PG network  definition,  EIV  method,
              EIV evaluation window, list of scenarios, and their setting.

       -db_mapping <filename>
              Specifies the name of the file that contains the mapping between
              a scenario and its corresponding rail analysis directory.

              Following is a snippet of the mapping file:

              SCENARIO_1   RailDir/latest

              SCENARIO_2   RailDir/latest

       -domain  <name>
              (Mandatory) Specifies the name of the power domain.

       -hier_block_instance  <names>
              Specifies  the list of instances of the master block that are to
              be repaired or reported.  This parameter is specified  with  the
              -hierarchical  parameter. When the instances are specified using
              this parameter, only the specified instances are repaired or re-
              ported.

       -hierarchical {true | false}
              Specifies to run the hierarchical  repair  flows  (reinforce_pg,
              IR-aware  placement,  and  ECO).  When  this parameter is set to
              true, you must specify at least one state directory in the  con-
              figuration file.

              Default: false

       -import_analysis_data {true | false}
              Specifies  to import the existing rail analysis results. If this
              parameter is set to true, you must specify at  least  one  state
              directory in the configuration file specified with -config.

              Default: false

       -ir_effort {high||medium||low}
              Specifies  the  effort  level  for running IR repair. The effort
              level for IR repair can be set to high, medium, or low.  By  de-
              fault,  the level is set to high. If there is an impact on Qual-
              ity of Results (QOR), you may choose to lower the effort level.

              Default: high

              To achieve optimal results, a balance between IR and timing  ef-
              forts  is crucial. The default setting is high IR and low timing
              effort, which generally provides the best IR fix rate.  However,
              if  there  is  a  degradation in timing, you should increase the
              timing effort to safeguard it. If the timing  continues  to  de-
              grade even with a high timing effort, then you should reduce the
              IR effort.

       -nParallel <value>
              Specifies  the  number  of scenarios or databases that are to be
              analyzed.

       -scenario_default <list>
              Specifies the list of default scenarios or databases.

       -skip  Skips  user-defined  instances  specified  with  -watch_box  and
              -watch_instances.

       -timing_effort {high||medium||low}
              Specifies  the  effort  level the software uses for timing opti-
              mization.  The effort level for  timing  can  be  set  to  high,
              medium,  or  low.  By default, the level is set to low to ensure
              best IR fix. If timing degrades, you may choose to increase  the
              effort level.

              To  achieve optimal results, a balance between IR and timing ef-
              forts is crucial. The default setting is high IR and low  timing
              effort,  which generally provides the best IR fix rate. However,
              if there is a degradation in timing,  you  should  increase  the
              timing  effort  to  safeguard it. If the timing continues to de-
              grade even with a high timing effort, then you should reduce the
              IR effort.

       -watch_box <filename>
              Specifies a file containing the list of  regions,  wherein  only
              the  instances  inside  these  regions will be reported. You can
              write multiple regions in the file.

              The format of the file is:

               {{x1,y1}{x2,y2}}

               {{x3,y3}{x4,y4}}

       -watch_inst <filename>
              Specifies a file containing the list of instances to be reported
              for IR repair. You can write multiple instances in the file.

              The format of the file is:

               instance_1

              Instance_2

Examples
              * The following command runs  2  scenarios  with  different  eiv
                method, eiv_eval_window, and thresholds for each instance type
                (clock and data):

                set_voltus_insight_mode  -config  insight.config  -domain  ALL
                -db_mapping db_mapping.txt

                Following is a snippet from the  insight.config  file:####  PG
                Network Definition ###

                Nets VDD VSS

                Domain_1 ALL  VDD   VSS

                #### Global Options ###

                eiv_eval_window {}

                eiv_method {}

                #### Scenario Definition ###

                SCENARIO_DEFAULT: SCENARIO_1  SCENARIO_2

                #### Scenarion Setting ###

                SCENARIO_1

                   eiv_eval_window elapse

                   eiv_method Worst

                   Domain Domain_1

                        threshold_data 0.4

                        threshold_clock 0.4

                   Net VSS

                        threshold_data 0.09

                        threshold_clock 0.09

                   Net VDD

                        threshold_data 0.81

                        threshold_clock 0.81

                SCENARIO_2

                   eiv_eval_window switching

                   eiv_method WorstAvg

                   Domain Domain_1

                        threshold_data 0.4

                        threshold_clock 0.4

                   Net VSS

                        threshold_data 0.09

                        threshold_clock 0.09

                   Net VDD

                        threshold_data 0.81

                        threshold_clock 0.81

